    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Carrie Nation will be in Spokane\nthe first four days in May, accord\ning to plans outlined in letter re-\nceived from her by Mrs. A. J. AL\nbring, a prominent w. c. T. U.\nworker, here this week. In the let\nter to Mrs. Albring was tiny gold\nRatchet, engraved Carrie Nation,\nHome Defender\" Mrs. Albring\nsays the union will cooperate with\nMrs. Nation in her work here. The\nnotorious temperance advocate is\nnow in South Dakota, where she\nwill remain until after the cam\npaign against rum is over there.\nFrom Spokane she will journey to\nSeattle."
    }
  ]
